    <h2>Explore Tarot Tournaments and Compete for Glory</h2>

	<h3>The Tournament Format</h3>
	<p>Tarot tournaments are an exciting opportunity for players to showcase their skills in a competitive environment. Each tournament features games for 4 or 5 players, where participants pay a buy-in—250, 500, or 1000 tokens—to enter. The tournament begins with the quarterfinals, and players must win to advance to the semifinals and then to the final match. Each match is critical; losing eliminates you from the tournament. Only the best will claim victory and secure their spot on the leaderboard!</p>

	<h3>How Rankings Work</h3>
	<p>Participants play three intense matches during the tournament. The total points scored across all three games determine the final ranking of each player. At the end of the tournament, an exclusive leaderboard displays the top 100 players, showcasing their performance. This ranking system ensures that consistency and skill are rewarded. Will you rise to the challenge and secure a spot among the top players?</p>

	<h3>Learn the Rules</h3>
	<p>Not sure about the specifics of the tournament? Visit the dedicated <a href="#">Rules</a> section to understand the format, scoring system, and strategies to succeed. Whether you’re a seasoned pro or a newcomer, the rules will help you master the game and prepare for the competition.</p>

	<h3>Prizes for the Top Players</h3>
	<p>What’s a tournament without exciting rewards? Check out the Rewards sectioncin the game to discover the prizes awaiting the top 100 players. From exclusive items to in-game currency, the stakes are high, and the competition is fierce. The higher you rank, the greater the rewards. Will you claim the ultimate prize and make your mark in the Tarot community?</p>
